  CurrentLogLevel: 3
  m_statusReadOnly: 
  _toolName: TaskOrganizer
  _toolPriority: 0
  _descriptionForPrompt: 'Use this tool to manage the assistant''s internal to-do
    list.


    The to-do list represents short-term tasks the user wants to track.
    Tasks are small, practical items such as work tasks, personal reminders, domestic
    chores, hobby goals, or tasks related to improving the assistant itself.


    Use
    this tool when the user:

    - asks to add a task

    - asks to remove or delete
    a task

    - asks to rename or modify a task

    - asks to change a task''s
    status

    - asks to change category, priority, or urgency

    - asks to update
    notes for a task


    Tasks are identified by an integer taskId.


    Important
    rules:

    - Do NOT invent tasks unless the user explicitly asks to add one.

    -
    When creating a task, the taskId is assigned automatically by the system.

    -
    Task names should be short and clear (maximum 128 characters).

    - Notes should
    be short descriptors, not long logs (maximum ~256 characters).

    - The tool
    accepts either a single action object OR an array of action objects.

    - If
    no category, priority, or urgency is defined, set to "UNDEFINED"

    - if no
    status is defined, assume "PENDING"


    Available actions:

    createTask

    deleteTask

    rename

    setCategory

    setPriority

    setUrgency

    setStatus

    setNotes


    Enum
    values:


    category:

    UNDEFINED

    WORK

    PERSONAL

    HOBBY

    DOMESTIC

    RITSUKO


    priority:

    UNDEFINED

    LOW

    MEDIUM

    HIGH


    urgency:

    UNDEFINED

    LOW

    MEDIUM

    HIGH


    status:

    PENDING

    INPROGRESS

    BLOCKED

    DONE

    CANCELLED

    ARCHIVED


    Prefer
    batching multiple actions into a single payload array if several changes are
    needed at once.


    Finally, always call the ToDoListDisplayTool whenever we
    make any changes to the to-do list, default display time of five minutes. Because
    the tool priority is defined, this will always deterministically run after to-do
    list changes have been made.'
  _jsonPayloadExampleForPrompt: "A valid single action example:\n\n{\n  \"action\":
    \"createTask\",\n  \"name\": \"Investigate webcam timeout issue\",\n  \"category\":
    \"WORK\",\n  \"priority\": \"HIGH\",\n  \"urgency\": \"MEDIUM\",\n  \"status\":
    \"INPROGRESS\",\n  \"notes\": \"Testing overnight with C910 camera\"\n}\n\n\n{\n 
    \"action\": \"createTask\",\n  \"name\": \"Task A\",\n  \"category\": \"UNDEFINED\",\n 
    \"priority\": \"UNDEFINED\",\n  \"urgency\": \"UNDEFINED\",\n  \"status\": \"PENDING\",\n 
    \"notes\": \"Seems to be a vaguely defined task\"\n}\n\nA valid task status update:\n\n{\n 
    \"action\": \"setStatus\",\n  \"taskId\": 12,\n  \"status\": \"INPROGRESS\"\n}\n\n\nA
    valid rename example:\n\n{\n  \"action\": \"rename\",\n  \"taskId\": 12,\n  \"name\":
    \"Investigate webcam USB timeout\"\n}\n\n\nA valid multi-action example:\n\n[\n 
    {\n    \"action\": \"createTask\",\n    \"name\": \"Fix Ritsuko task prompt formatting\",\n   
    \"category\": \"RITSUKO\",\n    \"priority\": \"HIGH\",\n    \"urgency\": \"MEDIUM\"\n 
    },\n  {\n    \"action\": \"setStatus\",\n    \"taskId\": 7,\n    \"status\":
    \"DONE\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"action\": \"setNotes\",\n    \"taskId\": 4,\n    \"notes\":
    \"Blocked waiting for hardware test results\"\n  }\n]"
